import matplotlib.pyplot as plt
import pandas as pd
def plot(data: pd.DataFrame):
    data['date'] = pd.to_datetime(data['date'], errors='coerce')
    data = data.groupby('date')['price'].mean().reset_index()
    plt.plot(data['date'], data['price'])
    plt.axhline(y=data['price'].mean(), color='r', linestyle='-')
    plt.title('What is the average price of stocks over the years?', wrap=True)
    plt.legend(['Price', 'Average Price'])
    return plt;

chart = plot(data)

import matplotlib.pyplot as plt
import pandas as pd
def plot(data: pd.DataFrame):
    data['price'].plot(kind='hist', bins=50, color='blue', edgecolor='black', alpha=0.7)
    plt.axvline(data['price'].mean(), color='red', linestyle='dashed', linewidth=1, label=f"Mean: {data['price'].mean():0.2f}")
    plt.axvline(data['price'].median(), color='green', linestyle='dashed', linewidth=1, label=f"Median: {data['price'].median():0.2f}")
    plt.legend()
    plt.title('What is the distribution of stock prices?', wrap=True)
    return plt;

chart = plot(data)

import matplotlib.pyplot as plt
import pandas as pd
def plot(data: pd.DataFrame):
    data['date'] = pd.to_datetime(data['date'], format='%Y-%m-%d', errors='coerce')
    stock_prices = data.groupby('symbol')['price'].max().sort_values(ascending=False)
    fig, ax = plt.subplots(figsize=(10, 6))
    ax.bar(stock_prices.index, stock_prices.values, color='blue')
    ax.set_xlabel('Stock Symbol')
    ax.set_ylabel('Price')
    ax.axhline(stock_prices.max(), color='red', linestyle='--', label=f'Highest Price: {stock_prices.max():.2f}')
    ax.legend()
    plt.title('Which stock had the highest price?', wrap=True)
    return plt;

chart = plot(data)
